OPUS LANE — DONE (second pass). Root is now empty; all test infra lives in dedicated folders.

WHAT WAS DELIVERED:
  Agents/           — FakeAgentBase + 6 fakes (Echo, Replay, MultiMessage, TextStreaming, RoleCheck, Delegating)
                       All inherit FakeAgentBase. TimeProvider injected by ctor.
  ChatClients/      — FakeChatClient (kept), ChatMessageExtensions, AsyncEnumerableExtensions
  Conformance/      — IAgentFixture, IChatClientAgentFixture, AgentTestBase<TFixture>,
                       RunTests, RunStreamingTests, ChatClientAgentRunTests, StructuredOutputRunTests,
                       MenuPlugin, CityInfo, Support/(AgentCleanup, SessionCleanup, ConformanceConstants)
                       All [Fact] methods use TestContext.Current.CancellationToken (xUnit v3 pattern).
                       All `await using` uses .ConfigureAwait(false).

WHAT WAS DROPPED:
  Workflows/        — Microsoft.Agents.AI.Workflows is NOT centrally managed and AGENTS.md forbids
                       new packages. Agent test infra and workflow test infra need to live in two
                       packages; this one stays cohesively about agents. Full design lives in
                       noty/Generic/* if you want to ship it as a separate package later.

STILL FREE FOR YOU:
  Hosting/          — Kestrel in-memory, AGUITestServer (currently at root)
  Logging/          — XunitLoggerProvider, LoggedTestBase, LogAssert, CapturingLoggerProvider, TestOutputAdapter (root)
  Http/             — RecordingHttpMessageHandler, FaultingStreamHandler, FakeHttpMessageHandler (root),
                       RecordedRequest (root), SseResponseParser (root)
  Diagnostics/      — ActivityCollector (root)
  BitNet/           — BitNetAttribute, BitNetFixture, BitNetTestGroup (root)
  noty/             — harvest area; csproj excludes it from compile

CONVENTIONS I FOLLOWED:
  - net10.0, C# 14, nullable, file-scoped namespaces
  - TimeProvider.System for any time access (no banned clock APIs)
  - No new packages added to Directory.Packages.props
  - No analyzer suppressions
  - No FluentAssertions (used Xunit Assert directly)
  - Namespace = folder. Cross-folder references add explicit usings.

COORDINATION:
  AGUITestServer.cs at the root now imports `using ...AgentTesting.Agents` to see FakeTextStreamingAgent.
  When you move it into Hosting/, keep that using.
